Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.57,0:01:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Operations Midway and Aleutian were carried out in June 1942 with the main force of the Japanese Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.98,0:01:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Midway has been a major defeat for the Japanese since the beginning of the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.93,0:01:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but the Aleutian Operation was able to occupy Attu and Kiska without any resistance from the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.13,0:02:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiska Withdrawal (Episode 16)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.24,0:02:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiska Island is about 40km long and about 10km wide and is closed to ice and snow all year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.52,0:02:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in the summer, it is often covered with thick fog and the temperature is below freezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.89,0:02:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the first place, the purpose of the Japanese Army's Operation Aleutian
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.22,0:02:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,was to stop the advance of the American MTF from the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.86,0:02:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,On Kiska Island, there were about 5,600 Army and Navy soldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.05,0:02:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,under the command of the North Sea garrison commander and Major General Mineki.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.84,0:02:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.30,0:02:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,According to reports from Northern Command's reconnaissance planes,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.36,0:02:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the enemy unknowingly built an air base on the neighboring island of Amchitka.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.95,0:02:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.04,0:02:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that the United States is on the offensive from the battle on Guadalcanal Island in the south,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:03:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but has it finally reached the north?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately 90 nautical miles from Amchitka Island to Kiska Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.12,0:03:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, Attu Island will also be hit harder than it is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.71,0:03:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiska Island and Attu Island are important bases in the north for us. We absolutely have to protect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.42,0:03:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an air raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.62,0:03:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Headquarters immediately began transporting reinforcements to Attu Island and Kiska Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.70,0:03:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,On May 11th,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.22,0:03:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately 11,000 US troops escorted by the US North Pacific fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.32,0:04:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,under Major General Thomas Kinkade, began landing on Attu Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.36,0:04:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The garrison captain, Colonel Yamazaki, and less than 2,500 Japanese soldiers fought back fiercely,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.10,0:04:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but on May 30th, they were finally wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.92,0:04:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the first Japanese army to die via banzai charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.07,0:04:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The US military, which regained Attu Island from the Japanese army,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.30,0:04:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,set up a fleet blockade in the North Pacific to block the isolated island of Kiska.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.86,0:04:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Headquarters finally ordered a submarine withdrawal from the isolated island of Kiska,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.12,0:04:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but the US Pacific Fleet's scrutiny made the withdrawal operation difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.44,0:04:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy attacks are becoming more intense day by day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.97,0:05:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The landing on Kiska Island will begin shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.53,0:05:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that, we have to complete the withdrawal without leaving any soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.61,0:05:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy's vigilance is strict.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.34,0:05:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Several submarines have already been sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How many have successfully withdrawn via submarine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.14,0:05:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,820 out of 5,639. {Not sure why this line is so long, but is as HA has it, perhaps we should split this into two lines to remove this weird pause.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.46,0:05:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.52,0:05:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It is 15%?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Only about 80 people can be loaded on a submarine at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.39,0:05:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Staff officer Fuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.39,0:05:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Please go to Paramushir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like the you to advise the Northern Command to withdraw everyone at once by surface ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.73,0:05:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be the final meeting on the withdrawal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.38,0:05:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,On June 16th, the submarine carrying Staff officer Fujii escaped Kiska Island safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,On the 20th, he arrived at the Chishima Islands, Paramushir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:06:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Northern Command of the Navy was anchored at the port of Paramushir Island
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.55,0:06:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,under the command of Vice Admiral Kawase's 5th Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.71,0:06:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The local commander strongly desires to withdraw by surface ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.97,0:06:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently there has been a lot of damage to our submarines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.86,0:06:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Withdrawal by submarines must be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.74,0:06:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Can a large number of ships escape the eyes of the enemy's strict surveillance and go to Kiska Island?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, we cannot expect the support of the aviation unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is clearly reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,On Kiska Island, 5,000 comrades are holding out under the fierce attack of the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to make the same mistake we made on Attu Island?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.01,0:06:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes at least 10 days to go to Kiska Island and come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.41,0:06:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It is almost impossible for a large fleet to act without replenishing by tanker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.98,0:07:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not confident in the Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.23,0:07:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is something that can protect the ships of our large fleet, it will be solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.64,0:07:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, our fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.00,0:07:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.12,0:07:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Beard of Kimura. {Pretty sure it is this guy: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masatomi_Kimura, the stache is a dead giveaway, the ship is https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_cruiser_Abukuma see more info here: http://www.combinedfleet.com/abukuma_t.htm}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.56,0:07:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Beard of Kimura is the captain who assumed command of the flagship Abukuma 10 days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.59,0:07:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A sailor who just assumed command of the First Destroyer Squadron: Major General Kimura.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.11,0:07:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.68,0:07:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big role.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.95,0:07:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy has an excellent radio detector.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.61,0:07:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There is also a strategy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.91,0:07:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.41,0:07:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the ancient Japanese ninjutsu techniques, the technique of fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.91,0:07:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.41,0:08:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiska Island is a foggy place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.05,0:08:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It is advantageous to act using the fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.04,0:08:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.28,0:08:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the Kiska Island withdrawal operation, which relies on the fog of the North Sea, proceeded steadily.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.52,0:08:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest weapon of the withdrawal operation is fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In August, the fog will fade.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.89,0:08:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do this, we should complete it by mid-July.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.82,0:08:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How many Daithatsu-class landing craft are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.69,0:08:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,About 10 ships can be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.52,0:08:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes time to transport by itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.19,0:08:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's load 12 ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.18,0:08:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest problem is the meeting point and meeting time of the local army.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.87,0:08:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we can approach Kiska Island but make a mistake in our meeting time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The meeting point is Kiska Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.28,0:08:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The meeting time is five days after the day from when our rescue fleet sails.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.17,0:08:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about 3 hours after sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.18,0:08:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the fog clears and we can't get close that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:09:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Have them try again every day. At that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.28,0:09:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The withdrawal operation is a covert action.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.94,0:09:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful when contacting the local army.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.32,0:09:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The rescue fleet decided to set sail on July 7th.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.13,0:09:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Our garrison will meet at Kiska Port at sunset on the 11th.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.24,0:09:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not leave a single soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.70,0:09:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When will the rescue fleet arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.02,0:09:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't come so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.15,0:09:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we suffer the same fate as Attu Island?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.80,0:09:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,July 7th, 1943, the rescue fleet under the command of Major General Kimura is:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.31,0:10:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,two light cruisers, ten destroyers, one tanker, and one landing ship. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.64,0:10:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,With a total of 14 ships, they left via Kuril Islands, rather than the port.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.46,0:10:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The fog condition looks good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.89,0:10:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, optimism is not allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.14,0:10:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in the fog, if the enemy finds us, everything is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.64,0:10:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay outside 500 nautical miles from the enemy air base.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.86,0:10:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The rescue fleet reached 500 nautical miles southwest of Kiska Island on July 12th,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.80,0:10:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as scheduled. It finished refueling, and turned its course to Kiska Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.57,0:10:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,However, at the time of the decision, the fog cleared up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.38,0:10:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an ironic prank of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.42,0:10:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:10:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We've come this far with a preparedness for death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.09,0:10:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, they are urging you to come all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.54,0:11:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we approach Kiska Island, the fog may come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.70,0:11:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you go back to the waiting point and wait for that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.70,0:11:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't. There is not enough fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.49,0:11:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, why don't you turn back and try again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.04,0:11:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't be able to do that either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.42,0:11:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The current issues is fuel shortage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.10,0:11:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Even trying twice is too much for a fleet this large. {HA had: "Even trying twice is too much for this big family."}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, are you condemning the Kiska Island garrison?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.62,0:11:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.95,0:12:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.86,0:12:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Lets go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.72,0:12:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We can come back again if we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.40,0:12:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That day, the Kiska Island garrison, which was waiting for the rescue fleet, soon received
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.02,0:12:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a brief description of the cancellation of their withdrawal operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.30,0:12:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiska Island was once again in despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.88,0:12:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What came to their mind was the appearance of their comrades smashed on Attu Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.50,0:13:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.85,0:13:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How about taking advantage of this Opportunity?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.70,0:13:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, do you want to attack this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.18,0:13:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, it was already too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm here. I was just a little careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.54,0:13:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The key to winning or losing is to be a little careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.88,0:13:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.63,0:13:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fog is occurring from Paramushir to Aleutian.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.01,0:13:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How many days will it last?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.88,0:13:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Five days probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.84,0:13:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.98,0:13:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.84,0:13:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What day is it today?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.81,0:13:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It is July 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.31,0:13:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.64,0:14:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, let's skip the story to July 30th, about 10 days after July 19th,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.15,0:14:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and explain the situation on the US military's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,From this day, the American North Pacific Fleet began a naval bombardment on Kiska Island every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.33,0:14:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The landing of the US military on Kiska Island is finally approaching. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.34,0:14:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The area around Kiska Island was completely blocked by the American North Pacific Fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.24,0:14:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,making it completely impossible for the Japanese fleet to approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.44,0:14:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,On August 14th, US troops finally launched a landing operation on Kiska Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.58,0:14:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of participating ships was 91,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.15,0:14:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the number of troops exceeded 34,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did the Japanese army go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.31,0:15:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they escaped into the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,On Kiska Island, there were only three stray dogs and no Japanese garrison.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, 25 American soldiers were killed by friendly fire and 31 were injured due to anxiety and fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.17,0:16:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How about 5,000 Japanese garrison soldiers escaped under US military surveillance
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.52,0:16:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and withdrew into the North Sea fog was a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.38,0:16:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Lets return to the Japanese military side on July 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.90,0:16:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.48,0:16:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.98,0:16:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fog is occurring from Paramushir to Aleutian.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.48,0:16:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How many days will it last?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.62,0:16:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, I think this is the last fog. {This is what HA has, but it seems wrong, why is he not saying 5 here like he did earlier}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.50,0:16:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.02,0:16:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.26,0:17:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What day is it today?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.82,0:17:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is July 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.04,0:17:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On July 22nd, the rescue fleet for the second withdrawal operation left Paramushir in the thick fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.76,0:17:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.68,0:17:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want it to clear up as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.27,0:17:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,On the light tour ship, Staff officer Fujii prayed for the safety of his comrades on Kiska Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.23,0:17:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I will show you success this time. Please wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.84,0:17:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If the enemy lands, I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Only you guys will be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The rescue fleet has left Paramushir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.42,0:17:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, I can finally go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.96,0:17:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.56,0:17:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.72,0:18:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.23,0:18:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a telegram saving that they would leave today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.56,0:18:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kiska Island defenders were delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.78,0:18:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,However, two American destroyers were still watching at the entrance to Kiska bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.18,0:18:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Around that time, one US military reconnaissance aircraft caught sight of seven ships that seemed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.29,0:18:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the Japanese fleet on radar 200 nautical miles southwest of Attu Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.10,0:18:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the US North Pacific fleet gathered at the point indicated by the reconnaissance aircraft on July 25th,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.67,0:18:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,preparing to ambush the Japanese fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.66,0:18:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they were actually bombarding a Japanese ghost fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.46,0:18:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The American side was unaware of their radar error.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.86,0:19:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What radar thought was a Japanese fleet was an echo on a nearby island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.18,0:19:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The bombardment fired more than 1,000 shells into the cold North Pacific waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.26,0:19:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, the Japanese rescue fleet was waiting while replenishing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.26,0:19:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at a point about 500 nautical miles, far southwest of Kiska Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn. The fog cleared up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.08,0:19:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Same as the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.95,0:19:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The foggy season may have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.12,0:19:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was late to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.74,0:19:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, if nothing is done, we will be immediately discovered by enemy reconnaissance aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.69,0:19:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If we are attacked, everything is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.29,0:19:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kiska Island garrison contacted us. They have reported that the weather on the 29th is definitely foggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.63,0:19:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe that fog will come out in this weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.98,0:20:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's a great opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.42,0:20:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Start towards Kiska Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.66,0:20:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.86,0:20:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's like jumping into the enemy's pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.36,0:20:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When an enemy fleet comes out,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.64,0:20:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we will fire and withdraw then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,On July 29th,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.68,0:20:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,fog miraculously covered the North Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.48,0:20:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The US North Pacific fleet, which bombarded the Japanese ghost fleet and consumed fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.48,0:20:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,gathered at 105 nautical miles south-southeast of Kiska Island to refuel all ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.76,0:20:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, Kiska Island's surveillance disappeared and at this moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.14,0:20:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Major General Kimura decided and the rescue fleet rushed into Kiska Bay in the fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.51,0:21:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A ship has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.53,0:21:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Japanese ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.65,0:21:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. We can go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.28,0:21:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please see, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.48,0:21:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The happy faces of those soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.58,0:21:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was good
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.68,0:22:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The last landing craft has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.58,0:22:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, thank you for your patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.28,0:22:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.76,0:22:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately 5,000 Kiska Island garrison members have completed their withdrawal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.47,0:22:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It took only 35 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.74,0:23:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this lucky withdrawal of Kiska just a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.54,0:23:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of the first withdrawal operation, if Kimura made a reckless decision and made the decision to go in,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.14,0:23:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he would surely be under the scrutiny of the US military and there is no doubt that he would be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.31,0:23:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the worst case, a commander must not lose his composure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.44,0:23:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A calm decision maker that should always look at all possibilities and lead them to success can really be of value.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.28,0:23:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,On August 1st, the rescue fleet safely arrived at Paramushir Port.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.80,0:23:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, as before, US troops continued to bombard the ghost defense forces on Kiska Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.82,0:23:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,astonishing the three dogs.
